{
  "page": "A Clash of Kings (comics)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #DEDEE2; text-align:center; font-style: italic;\">George R.R. Martin's A Clash of Kings</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Landry_Walker\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Landry Walker\">Landry Walker</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:United States\">United States</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_language\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:English language\">English</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Series</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre(s)</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fantasy\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Fantasy\">Fantasy</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamite_Entertainment\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Dynamite Entertainment\">Dynamite Entertainment</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Released</th><td>\n7 June 2017 – 24 November 2021</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Illustrator</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mel_Rubi\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Mel Rubi\">Mel Rubi</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Cover Artist</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_S._Miller\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Mike S. Miller\">Mike S. Miller</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media Type</th><td>\nComics</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Preceded&#160;by</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones_(comics)\" title=\"A Game of Thrones (comics)\">George R.R. Martin's A Game of Thrones</a></i></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>George R.R. Martin's A Clash of Kings</b></i> is a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/comic_book\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:comic book\">comic book</a> adaptation of <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>'s fantasy novel <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, the second in the <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i> series. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Production\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Production</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Publication_history\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publication history</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Collections\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Collections</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References_and_Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References and Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Production\">Production</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Clash_of_Kings_(comics)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Production\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The comic book series is scripted by comic book writer <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Landry_Walker\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Landry Walker\">Landry Walker</a> and drawn by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mel_Rubi\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Mel Rubi\">Mel Rubi</a>, with covers by Rubi and by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_S._Miller\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Mike S. Miller\">Mike S. Miller</a>. It is intended to follow the story and atmosphere of the novel closely, at a rate of about a page of art for each page of text. It covered 32 issues of 29 pages each.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publication_history\">Publication history</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Clash_of_Kings_(comics)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Publication history\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The initial issue was published by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamite_Entertainment\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Dynamite Entertainment\">Dynamite Entertainment</a> in June 2017, almost 3 years after the conclusion of the previous adaptation, <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones_(comics)\" title=\"A Game of Thrones (comics)\">George R.R. Martin's A Game of Thrones</a></i>. New issues were published at a rate of one per month. Sixteen issues were released until March 2019, when the series went on hiatus. In January 2020, the adaptation continued in a new volume, marketed as A Clash of Kings, Part II. The series concluded with the 16th issue of the second volume on November 24, 2021.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Collections\">Collections</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Clash_of_Kings_(comics)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Collections\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Four sets of eight issues each were published by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bantam_Books\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Bantam Books\">Bantam Books</a> as <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trade_paperback_(comics)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Trade paperback (comics)\">trade paperbacks</a>, marketed as a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/graphic_novel\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:graphic novel\">graphic novel</a>. \n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Title</th>\n<th>ISBN</th>\n<th>Date of publication</th>\n<th>Contains\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><i>A Clash of Kings: The Graphic Novel: Volume One</i>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/index.php/Special:BookSources/978-0-440-42324-9\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-440-42324-9\">978-0-440-42324-9</a>\n</td>\n<td>October 17, 2018\n</td>\n<td><i>A Clash of Kings</i> #1-8\n<p>The Making of <i>A Clash of Kings: The Graphic Novel: Volume One</i>\n</p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><i>A Clash of Kings: The Graphic Novel: Volume Two</i>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/index.php/Special:BookSources/978-0-440-42325-6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-440-42325-6\">978-0-440-42325-6</a>\n</td>\n<td>October 1, 2019\n</td>\n<td><i>A Clash of Kings</i> #9-16\n<p>The Making of <i>A Clash of Kings: The Graphic Novel: Volume Two</i>\n</p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><i>A Clash of Kings: The Graphic Novel: Volume Three</i>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/index.php/Special:BookSources/978-0-440-42326-3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-440-42326-3\">978-0-440-42326-3</a>\n</td>\n<td>November 2, 2021\n</td>\n<td><i>A Clash of Kings Part II</i> #1-8, listed as #17-24\n<p>The Making of <i>A Clash of Kings: The Graphic Novel: Volume Three</i>\n</p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><i>A Clash of Kings: The Graphic Novel: Volume Four</i>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/index.php/Special:BookSources/978-1-984-82078-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-984-82078-5\">978-1-984-82078-5</a>\n</td>\n<td>October 2, 2022\n</td>\n<td><i>A Clash of Kings Part II</i> #9–16, listed as #25-32\n<p>The Making of <i>A Clash of Kings: The Graphic Novel: Volume Four</i>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References_and_Notes\">References and Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Clash_of_Kings_(comics)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References and Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.dynamite.com/htmlfiles/viewProduct.html?PRO=C72513028822616011\">Dynamite Entertainment: <i>George R.R. Martin's A Clash of Kings</i> Vol. 2 #16</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Clash_of_Kings_(comics)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: External links\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.dynamite.com/htmlfiles/viewProduct.html?CAT=DF-A_Clash_Of_Kings\"><i>George R.R. Martin's A Clash of Kings</i> at Dynamite Entertainment</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.dynamite.com/htmlfiles/viewProduct.html?CAT=DF-A_Clash_Of_Kings_Vol_2\"